Creating Long-Term Value Thru Relentless InnovationÂ®

ATI is a global manufacturer of technically advanced specialty materials and complex components. Our products support diverse markets and industries such as aerospace and defense, oil & gas, electrical energy, medical, automotive, and other industrial markets.
Summary:
ATI Millersburg is seeking an Engineer II, Quality to join our team. If you are looking for an opportunity to support a growing, world-class manufacturing company with multiple manufacturing operations, then this position is for you!
Essential Functions:
Lead Continuous Improvement activities and events to reduce quality incidents and improve process capability
Facilitate problem solving and root cause analysis events with cross functional teams
Assess dispositions, corrections, and corrective actions on non-conformance incidents
Support contract review and quality planning activities
Contribute to process change, risk analysis, and PFMEA evaluations
Support customer audits on processes, products, and the quality system
Support the quality system through process ownership of a key aspect
Perform tasks as assigned by management

Because we are a federal government contractor, we have special restrictions placed on us for hiring foreign nationals into certain key positions within the company. This particular position requires U.S. citizenship and the ability to obtain a Security Clearance.
ATI and its subsidiary companies will provide equal employment opportunities to all applicants without regard to applicant's race, color, religion, sex, gender, genetic information, national origin, age, veteran status, disability status, or any other status protected be federal or state law. The company will provide reasonable accommodations to allow an applicant to participate in the hiring process if so requested.

Requires BS in Manufacturing, Material Science, Mechanical, Chemical Engineering or associated four-year technical discipline
Ability to obtain a DOE Security Clearance is required
Preferred
Must have a strong aptitude for applying Engineering principles to solve manufacturing issues
Must have sound judgment and be able to plan, organize and control multiple activities simultaneously
Excellent communication skills (written and verbal) and the ability to interact well with employees and customers are essential
Demonstrated experience with computers, including MS Office suite
Technical background in quality systems, root cause analysis and continuous improvement is highly preferred
Familiarity with fundamental metalworking processes or experience in a manufacturing environment is also preferred

